items.name: Kamikaze-class Outfit Cosplay LoRA | Kantai Collection (Kancolle)
items.description:
This LoRA helps replicate the clothing style of Kamikaze-class destroyers from Kantai Collection (Kancolle). It's mainly meant for use with other characters & LoRA, and tries to give as much versatility to controlling the main outfit colors as possible, but there are some limitations.

Usage

This can be loaded as a "regular" LoRA and can be used at 0.7-1.0 weight effectively.

The LoRA was trained at 960x960 resolution so usage with highres fix to upscale is recommended.

Basic outfit prompt tags

[color_1] kimono, wide sleeves, anchor
BREAK [color_2] hakama, hakama skirt, long skirt

Replace [color_1] and [color_2] with your desired colors. Alternatively colors can be left to the model and it will probably veer towards colors in the training data as well as colors associated with your character (if any). You may need to add emphasis to get the desired coloration in some cases.

Even with separating the hakama prompt from the kimono prompt with BREAK, sometimes the colors will interfere with one other (especially green for some reason). In these cases, add "(([color] hakama))" or "(([color] kimono))" to the negative prompt to steer the process away from it.

Easy kimono colors: red, pink, white, light blue, light green

Easy hakama skirt colors: pink, red, black, blue, green

These are trained mainly using the actual Kamikaze-class images and a few cosplays so they're well-represented in training data.

Harder but possible kimono colors: orange, brown, grey, blue (not light blue), green (not light green), black

Harder but possible hakama colors: grey, brown, purple

Other colors: you can try but they probably won't work unless your character normally wears kimono/hakama in that color.

Note on tasuki

Tasuki (the ribbons tied around Kamikaze's shoulders that keeps her kimono sleeves up) can be prompted for, although they have a tendency to meld into nearby objects (particularly hair). Recommended tags:

((tasuki)), (short sleeves), over shoulder

If you don't want to depict tasuki but they appear anyways, try adding ((((tasuki)))) to negative. Also, specifically prompting for long sleeves can help.

Note on haori

The model was trained on images with characters wearing haoris (mainly Hatakaze's), but the base models don't understand the haori token well at all, so this LoRA didn't learn the word very well. But with some prompt engineering it's possible to get haoris in certain cases by using something like [yellow overcoat::0.4] with some trial and error.

Note on anchors

It's hard to control where the anchor appears because it's rather fluid in the base dataset.

In some cases, anchors may not appear, so increase weight on (anchor) in prompt if that's the case.

There does seem to be a tendency to draw anchors too low due to appearing off of the pattern on the lower skirt. Also, it's possible for the anchor to appear but not connect with the cloth properly. Unfortunately, retrying seems to be the easiest way to get the anchors to appear in the correct places.

Other notable tags

For your consideration

half updo, 
twin drills, drill hair
hair bow, hair ribbon, 
gradient sleeves,
floral print, 
cross-laced footwear, high heel boots, brown boots

Regarding actual Kamikaze-class ship girls

This wasn't intended as a character LoRA model, so I intentionally excluded the character tags. However, if you prompt for the individual characteristics enough you can probably get some somewhat convincing Kamikazes out.
